= TwitterShoes

* http://github.com/hone/twittershoes

== DESCRIPTION:

ruby script created to be a Twitter (http://www.twitter.com) client, 
that uses Shoes.rb (http://code.whytheluckystiff.net/shoes) to be run 
on various platforms (Linux, MacOSX, Windows). Shoes.rb is a winner !!

Please feel free to give a hand and produce some code, review it, fix bugs, etc.
--
In this fork, I've started some work to hide the twitter password on disk.  In the future I plan to add some UI features to request the user for a login/password.

The Current implementation

== REQUIREMENTS:

* Shoes.rb (http://github.com/why/shoes) installed on your operating system of choice.

== INSTALL:

* copy all *.rb files to a folder of yours
* fill in twitter username / password and crypto password (from above) at the beginning of the twittershoes.rb
* open tshoe.rb using Shoes
* after first run, can clear the twitter username/password

